在蘇丹[2010年總統大選](https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/sudan-
elections-2010/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/sudan-
elections-2010/")前夕，筆者為[資訊透明科技網絡](https://transparency.globalvoicesonline.org/
"https://transparency.globalvoicesonline.org/")專案[訪問](https://transparency.globalvoicesonline.org/project/sudan-
vote-monitor "https://transparency.globalvoicesonline.org/project/sudan-vote-
monitor")Fareed Zein，他領導公民選舉監督計畫[Sudan Vote
Monitor](http://sudanvotemonitor.com/ "http://sudanvotemonitor.com/")，Fareed
Zein希望藉由這項計畫，讓蘇丹二十多年來[初次民主選舉](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/12/sudan-
sudan-votes-after-24-years/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/12/sudan-
sudan-votes-
after-24-years/")更加透明，他提到在過去的政治事件中，「我們毫不清楚發生什麼事，我們希望點亮一盞燈，讓人們瞭解最偏遠投票所的情況」。筆者在4月28日訪問他，瞭解在選舉結束後，此刻對這項計畫的想法。

[![An official from Sudan's National Elections Commission \(left\) assists a
voter at a polling station in Juba, Sudan.](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/04/sudan_elections-300x203.jpg)](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/04/sudan_elections.jpg)

